22/02/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- More than 110 people in the Zajecar area were evacuated after the Beli Timok River rose to a record level as a result of snow melt, local media reported on Sunday (February 21st). 
As many as 250 homes have been flooded. 
Zajecar Mayor Bosko Nicic asked neighbouring municipalities for help and now the army is participating in the rescue operations. 
A railway line between Zajecar and Nis has been cut due to the flooding. 
(B92, Beta, Tanjug, RTS, Blic - 21/02/10)
